  ('commercial', 'Spectrum', '1100 Series Opaque Satin Glazes', '1123', 'Satin Speckle', 'Cone 4 / Cone 6', 'Smooth satin finish on these stoneware glazes which are also lead free, A/P non-toxic and dinnerware safe', 'https://www.spectrumglazes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1123.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Spectrum', '1100 Series Opaque Satin Glazes', '1124', 'Satin Wedgwood', 'Cone 4 / Cone 6', 'Smooth satin finish on these stoneware glazes which are also lead free, A/P non-toxic and dinnerware safe', 'https://www.spectrumglazes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1124.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Spectrum', '1100 Series Opaque Satin Glazes', '1126', 'Satin Black', 'Cone 4 / Cone 6', 'Smooth satin finish on these stoneware glazes which are also lead free, A/P non-toxic and dinnerware safe', 'https://www.spectrumglazes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1126.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Spectrum', '1100 Series Opaque Satin Glazes', '1127', 'Satin Turquoise', 'Cone 4 / Cone 6', 'Smooth satin finish on these stoneware glazes which are also lead free, A/P non-toxic and dinnerware safe', 'https://www.spectrumglazes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1127.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Spectrum', '1100 Series Reactive Glazes', '1111', 'Holly Green', 'Cone 4 / Cone 6', 'These reactive glazes are all lead free but they exceed the vanadium and/or copper threshold limit in the liquid un-fired state and therefore are not non-toxic. However, they are all food safe if fired to the proper firing temperature. They behave in the manner described above for Reactive Glazes. Also be aware that some of the colors, such as 1148, 1152, 1153, 1154, 1158, 1159, 1161, 1162, and particularly 1173 are more fluid and may run. Be more careful when using them on vertical surfaces. Use fewer coats towards the bottom of the piece', 'https://www.spectrumglazes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1111.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Spectrum', '1100 Series Reactive Glazes', '1113', 'Milk & Honey', 'Cone 4 / Cone 6', 'These reactive glazes are all lead free, non-toxic and dinnerware safe. They are formulated to produce reactions during the firing cycle which give very interesting and beautiful effects. The final appearance of the glaze is dependent on firing temperature, glaze thickness and the composition of the clay body being used. The same glaze can look quite different on different clay bodies. The samples shown on the color charts are 3 brush coats of glaze fired to cone 5 in an electric kiln on a white clay body. Different results should be expected in reduction', 'https://www.spectrumglazes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1113.jpg'),
  ('commercial', 'Spectrum', '1100 Series Reactive Glazes', '1115', 'Moonscape', 'Cone 4 / Cone 6', 'These reactive glazes are all lead free, non-toxic and dinnerware safe. They are formulated to produce reactions during the firing cycle which give very interesting and beautiful effects. The final appearance of the glaze is dependent on firing temperature, glaze thickness and the composition of the clay body being used. The same glaze can look quite different on different clay bodies. The samples shown on the color charts are 3 brush coats of glaze fired to cone 5 in an electric kiln on a white clay body. Different results should be expected in reduction', 'https://www.spectrumglazes.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1115.jpg'),
